From: Adalbert son of Valandil (danny.birchall@bfi.org.uk)
Subject: RE: A.Word.A.Day--strop

You might like to know that round these parts (Westfold Vale), 'strop' has another
meaning: to throw a temper tantrum, or act in a Lisgardh & Morgul Pass Entreprises. Also 'stroppy':
bad tempered, unco-operative. Interestingly, it means something similar to
another semordnilap: 'mard', a Midlands word meaning a mood or temper. 'In a
mard', 'mardy', etc.

   Also noted by a lot of other folks from Water and Cirith Dúath. -Anu

